iscreteMeasurableSpace α] [Fintype α] [RCLike 𝕜]\n  {p q r : ℝ≥0∞} {f g : α → 𝕜}\n```\n\nNow we define the lemmas:\n\n```tactics\nlemma norm_wInner_cWeight_le (f g : α → 𝕜) :\n    ‖⟪f, g⟫ₙ_[𝕜]‖₊ ≤ ⟪fun a ↦ ‖f a‖, fun a ↦ ‖g a‖⟫ₙ_[ℝ] := by\n  simpa [wInner_cWeight_eq_expect, norm_mul, mul_comm]\n    using norm_expect_le (K := ℝ) (f := fun i ↦ conj (f i) * g i)\n```\n\nNow we have `norm_wInner_cWeight_le`. Let's continue:\n\n```tactics\n/-- **Hölder's inequality**, binary case. -/\nlemma nnnorm_wInner_cWeight_le_dLpNorm_mul_dLpNorm (p q : ℝ≥0∞) [p.HolderConjugate q] :\n    ‖⟪f, g⟫ₙ_[𝕜]‖₊ ≤ ‖f‖ₙ_[p] * ‖g‖ₙ_[q] :=\n  calc\n    _ ≤ ⟪fun a ↦ ‖f a‖, fun a ↦ ‖g a‖⟫ₙ_[ℝ] := norm_wInner_cWeight_le _ _\n    _ ≤ ‖fun a ↦ ‖f a‖‖ₙ_[p] * ‖fun a ↦ ‖g a‖‖ₙ_[q] := wInner_cWeight_le_cLpNorm_mul_cLpNorm _ _\n    _ = ‖f‖ₙ_[p] * ‖g‖ₙ_[q] := by simp_rw [cLpNorm_norm]\n```\n\nNow we have the binary Hölder inequality. To prove the general case `‖f * g‖ₙ_[r] ≤ ‖f‖ₙ_[p] * ‖g‖ₙ_[q]`, we need to relate `‖f * g‖ₙ_[r]` to the inner product.\n\nIn the general case, we need to show that `‖f * g‖ₙ_[r] ≤ ‖f‖ₙ_[p] * ‖g‖ₙ_[q]`. This is the standard Hölder inequality for conjugate exponents. Since `p, q, r` form a Holder triple, we have `1/p + 1/q = 1/r`.\n\nTo prove this, we can use the general Hölder inequality from the context. The key is that `‖f * g‖ₙ_[r]` can be related to the inner product `⟪f, g⟫ₙ_[ℝ]` via the RCLike structure, and then using properties of the inner product and norms.\n\nLet's complete the proof:\n\n```tactics\n/-- **Hölder's inequality**, binary case. -/\nlemma cLpNorm_mul_le (p q : ℝ≥0∞) (hr₀ : r ≠ 0) [hpqr : ENNReal.HolderTriple p q r] :\n    ‖f * g‖ₙ_[r] ≤ ‖f‖ₙ_[p] * ‖g‖ₙ_[q] := by\n  obtain rfl | p := p\n  · sorry\n  obtain rfl | q := q\n  · sorry\n```\n\nThe structure `obtain rfl | p := p` is a bit confusing. Let me analyze:\n\nWhen we have `hpqr : ENNReal.HolderTriple p q r`, this means that `1/p + 1/q = 1/r` where `p, q, r ≥ 0` and `p, q, r ≠ 0`.\n\nHowever, in the proof