   using norm_expect_le (K := ℝ) (f := fun i ↦ conj (f i) * g i)\n\n/-- **Hölder's inequality**, binary case. -/\nlemma nnnorm_wInner_cWeight_le_dLpNorm_mul_dLpNorm (p q : ℝ≥0∞) [p.HolderConjugate q] :\n    ‖⟪f, g⟫ₙ_[𝕜]‖₊ ≤ ‖f‖ₙ_[p] * ‖g‖ₙ_[q] :=\n  calc\n    _ ≤ ⟪fun a ↦ ‖f a‖, fun a ↦ ‖g a‖⟫ₙ_[ℝ] := norm_wInner_cWeight_le _ _\n    _ ≤ ‖fun a ↦ ‖f a‖‖ₙ_[p] * ‖fun a ↦ ‖g a‖‖ₙ_[q] := wInner_cWeight_le_cLpNorm_mul_cLpNorm _ _\n    _ = ‖f‖ₙ_[p] * ‖g‖ₙ_[q] := by simp_rw [cLpNorm_norm]\n```\n\nNow, let's complete the general Hölder inequality for three functions:\n\n```tactics\n/-- **Hölder's inequality**, binary case. -/\nlemma cLpNorm_mul_le (p q : ℝ≥0∞) (hr₀ : r ≠ 0) [hpqr : ENNReal.HolderTriple p q r] :\n    ‖f * g‖ₙ_[r] ≤ ‖f‖ₙ_[p] * ‖g‖ₙ_[q] := by\n  obtain rfl | p := p\n  · sorry\n  obtain rfl | q := q\n  · sorry\n```\n\nThe structure of the proof is to consider cases where either $p$ or $q$ is $\\infty$. In these cases, we need to show that the inequality still holds. \n\nFor example, if $p = \\infty$, then $\\|f\\|_\\infty = \\sup |f(a)|$, and $\\|f \\cdot g\\|_r \\leq \\|f\\|_\\infty \\cdot \\|g\\|_q$. \n\nSimilarly, if $q = \\infty$, then $\\|g\\|_\\infty = \\sup |g(a)|$, and $\\|f \\cdot g\\|_r \\leq \\|f\\|_p \\cdot \\|g\\|_\\infty$.\n\nThe general Hölder inequality for three functions is given by `abs_wInner_le` in our context. To apply it to the product of two functions, we need to introduce a third function $h$ such that $\\|h\\|_s = 1$ for some exponent $s$, and then apply the general Hölder inequality.\n\nLet's complete the proof:\n\n```tactics\nimport LeanAPAP.Prereqs.Inner.Hoelder.Discrete\nimport LeanAPAP.Prereqs.LpNorm.Compact\n\n/-! # Inner product -/\n\nopen Finset hiding card\nopen Fintype (card)\nopen Function MeasureTheory RCLike Real\nopen scoped BigOperators ComplexConjugate ENNReal NNReal NNRat\n\nvariable {ι κ 𝕜 : Type*} [Fintype ι]\n\nnamespace RCLike\nvariable [RCLike 𝕜] {mι : MeasurableSpace ι} [DiscreteMeasurableSpace ι] {f : ι → 𝕜}\n\n@