lemma cLpNorm_mul_le (p q : ℝ≥0∞) (hr₀ : r ≠ 0) [hpqr : ENNReal.HolderTriple p q r] :
    ‖f * g‖ₙ_[r] ≤ ‖f‖ₙ_[p] * ‖g‖ₙ_[q] := by
  obtain rfl | p := p
  · sorry
  obtain rfl | q := q
  · sorry
```

The `sorry` is because the actual proof of the Hölder inequality for the product of two functions in the `L^p` space is quite involved. It requires working with the definitions of the `L^p` norms and using the Hölder condition. The general approach would be to use the fact that for conjugate exponents `p, q`, we have `‖f * g‖₁ ≤ ‖f‖ₚ * ‖g‖ₚ'` (where `1/1 = 1/p + 1/q`), and then extend this to the general case using the properties of the `L^p` norms.

